document_data.History:
Dammasae was born on the [[Sword Coast]], per Gorstag,{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|354, 356-358|16}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|363, 365-367|20}} and per the [[Zhentarim]] [[Sememmon]], she spent her youth in [[Thunderstone]], [[Cormyr]].{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|270-271|13}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|282-283|16}} Before meeting Garthond, Dammasae was an adventurer and member of the Sorority of the Silver Fire who had already destroyed two [[dracolich]]es in the course of her adventuring.{{cite book/Heroes' Lorebook|111}}

She met Garthond ''en route'' to a Cult stronghold after being captured, bound, drugged, and gagged by Cult agents. The pair adventured together for a time, fell in love, and married in [[Baldur's Gate]]. She settled down in [[Elturel]] during her pregnancy, birth, and raising the infant Shandril until she was eight months old. The couple and their baby left for [[Shadowdale]] afterwards, together with Gorstag, in order to look for [[Syluné]]. However, they were ambushed by forces from the Cult at the [[Bridge of Fallen Men]], where Dammasae was mortally wounded, almost certainly in the {{yearlinkName|1340}}.

Gorstag saw to it that she received some healing in [[High Horn]] afterwards, but it was insufficient; they could not reach Syluné in time.{{cite book/Secrets of the Magister|58}} this was a little knoll on the north side of the road, close to the road west of [[Toad Knoll]] that was sacred to Mystra.{{cite book/Hall of Heroes|47}}
